@startuml
!theme plain
autonumber

box "User & Browser" #LightSteelBlue
    participant "End User" as User
    participant "Browser SPA Shell" as Browser
end box

box "Single Page App (Frontend)" #LightCoral
    participant "Router Views" as Router
    participant "Auth Service" as AuthService
    participant "State Store" as Store
    participant "API Client HTTP" as ApiClient
    participant "Service Worker Cache" as SW
    participant "Local Storage IndexedDB" as Storage
    participant "WebSocket Client" as WS
end box

box "Backend & Identity" #LightBlue
    participant "API Gateway Backend" as Backend
    participant "Identity Provider IAM" as IAM
    participant "Realtime Server WS" as Realtime
end box

' --- App load and cache ---
User -> Browser : 1. Open app (URL)
activate User
Browser -> SW : 1.1 Service Worker checks cache
activate SW
alt assets cached
    SW --> Browser : 1.2 Load app shell from cache
else
    Browser -> Backend : 1.3 GET static assets (CDN/server)
    Backend --> Browser : 1.4 Static assets (HTML, JS, CSS)
end
deactivate SW

Browser -> Router : 2. App bootstrap, Router initializes
activate Router
Router -> AuthService : 2.1 Check auth state (Store Storage)
activate AuthService
AuthService -> Storage : 2.2 Read tokens session
activate Storage
Storage --> AuthService : 2.3 Tokens profile found or empty
deactivate Storage
alt authenticated
    AuthService -> Store : 2.4 Set user session in state
    Store --> Router : 2.5 Route to protected view (Dashboard)
else
    Router --> Router : 2.6 Route to public view (Login)
end
deactivate AuthService

' --- Login (OIDC OAuth2 Authorization Code + PKCE) ---
User -> Router : 3. Click Login
activate Router
Router -> AuthService : 3.1 Initiate login flow
activate AuthService
opt using external IAM
    AuthService --> Browser : 3.2 Redirect to IAM authorize (PKCE)
    Browser -> IAM : 3.3 User authenticates at IAM
    IAM --> Browser : 3.4 Redirect back to SPA with code
    Browser -> AuthService : 3.5 Exchange code for tokens (POST token)
    AuthService -> IAM : 3.6 POST token (code+verifier)
    IAM --> AuthService : 3.7 Tokens (access_token, id_token, refresh_token)
end
AuthService -> Storage : 3.8 Persist tokens (memory secure storage)
AuthService -> ApiClient : 3.9 Set authorization header (Bearer)
AuthService -> ApiClient : 3.10 Fetch user profile (api me)
ApiClient -> Backend : 3.11 GET api me (Bearer token)
Backend --> ApiClient : 3.12 User profile
ApiClient --> Store : 3.13 Store profile & permissions
Store --> Router : 3.14 Redirect to initial protected route

' --- Data fetching and navigation ---
User -> Router : 4. Navigate to section (Vessels Ops Planning)
Router -> ApiClient : 4.1 Request resource via API client
ApiClient -> Backend : 4.2 GET api resource (Authorization: Bearer)
Backend --> ApiClient : 4.3 Data payload
ApiClient --> Store : 4.4 Update state
Store --> Router : 4.5 Views re-render with data

' --- Token refresh error handling ---
ApiClient -> AuthService : 5. On 401 or token exp try refresh
activate ApiClient
AuthService -> IAM : 5.1 Use refresh token or silent renew endpoint
activate IAM
IAM --> AuthService : 5.2 New access_token (or error)
deactivate IAM
AuthService -> Storage : 5.3 Update tokens
AuthService --> ApiClient : 5.4 Retry original request with new token
deactivate ApiClient

' --- Realtime updates ---
Browser -> WS : 6. Open WebSocket (with token)
activate WS
WS -> Realtime : 6.1 WS handshake auth
Realtime --> WS : 6.2 Push events (vessel updates, notifications)
WS --> Store : 6.3 Update state UI updates
deactivate WS

' --- Logout and revoke ---
User -> Router : 7. Click Logout
Router -> AuthService : 7.1 Clear state, storage
AuthService -> IAM : 7.2 Revoke token (optional: POST revoke)
IAM --> AuthService : 7.3 Revocation OK
AuthService --> Router : 7.4 Redirect to Login public view

' CORREÇÃO ABAIXO: Note usa intervalo (Store até Storage)
note over Store, Storage : Service Worker caches assets and API responses
note over ApiClient,AuthService : Exponential backoff, retry, centralised error handling

@enduml